      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_1112538" metaid="metaid_50" name="Phosphorylated STAT1, STAT3 form dimers" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">STATs can form dimers in the unphosphorylated state but only phosphorylated dimers are in the correct conformation to to bind consensus DNA sequences of target genes in the nucleus (Riech and Liu 2006).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
