      <reaction compartment="compartment_984" fast="false" id="reaction_1067651" metaid="metaid_52" name="IL6:IL6R-2 binds IL6ST:JAK1, JAK2, (TYK2)" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The complex of interleukin-6 (IL6) and the soluble, short form of the IL6 receptor (IL6R-2) binds to surface expressed IL6ST (gp130), a process known as trans signaling (Rose-John et al. 2006). This process is negatively regulated by the soluble form of IL6ST (IL6ST-2).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
