      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_1067688" metaid="metaid_55" name="IL6:IL6R binds IL6ST:JAK1,JAK2,(TYK2)" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The complex of interleukin-6 (IL6) bound to the IL6 receptor α subunit (IL6R) binds the IL-6 receptor β subunit IL6ST (gp130), which constitutively binds JAK kinases. Site II of IL6 interacts with the cytokine binding-homology region of IL6ST. Subsequently, site III of IL6 interacts with the IL6ST immunoglobulin-like activation domain.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
