      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_1112510" metaid="metaid_57" name="IL6ST is tyrosine phosphorylated" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Activated JAKs are believed to be responsible for phosphorylating the cytoplasmic region of IL6ST (gp130) (Wang and Fuller 1994, Reich and Liu 2006) creating docking sites for adaptor and downstream signaling molecules, in particular the factors STAT1 and STAT3. Several phosphotyrosine residues of IL6ST are docking sites for STATs (Stahl et al. 1995, Gerhartz et al. 1996). Tyr-759 phosphorylation allows recruitment of the phosphatase SHP2.</p>
        </notes>
